definitions.text: (cricket) the division of play during which six balls are bowled at the batsman by one player from the other team from the same end of the pitch
having come or been brought to a conclusion
examples: the affair is over, ended, finished

definitions.text: at or to a point across intervening space etc.
examples: come over and see us some time
he is known the world over

definitions.text: beyond the top or upper surface or edge; forward from an upright position

examples: the wallpaper was covered all over with flowers
everything was dusted over with a fine layer of soot
